cs.IT, cs.GT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM

The paper deals with the problem of channel allocation in wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-fields. However, the focus on frequency-selective interference channels and the use of game theory as the main tool for designing the algorithm suggest that cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.GT (Game Theory) are the most likely categories. Additionally, the distributed implementation of the algorithm and the analysis of its convergence properties suggest that cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also relevant sub-fields. Finally, the simulations carried out in the paper involve the use of fading channels, which are commonly studied in cs.MM (Multimedia).
